This paper is primarily focused on face attribute estimation using deep learning techniques, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The use of multi-task learning and convolutional neural networks also suggests a potential fit for the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves the use of crowdsourcing to obtain demographic attributes, which could potentially fall under the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. The use of deep learning and machine learning techniques also suggests a potential fit for the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves the evaluation of the proposed approach on a public-domain face database, which could potentially fall under the cryptography and security (cs.CR) sub-category.
